- Decisions with approval status
- Action items with assignee tracking 
- Blockers with dependency mapping
- Risks with impact assessments
- Ideas with categorization

## Document Model
Importance Score: 85/100

Core Structure:
- Document content with version tracking
- Bi-directional meeting references
- Signal extraction integration
- Transcript support for meeting summaries
- Document-signal relationship tracking

Key Features:
- Multi-source content integration
- Meeting context preservation
- Signal categorization system
- Historical tracking capabilities

## Relationship Structure
Importance Score: 80/100

Entity Relationships:
- Meetings ↔ Documents (bi-directional references)
- Meetings ↔ Signals (hierarchical categorization)
- Documents ↔ Signals (extraction context)
- Signals ↔ Signals (dependency mapping)

